I have dlib built and installed on my Ubuntu 16.04 LTS successfully. Now I am writing a program which link with it. An linking error occurs while function dlib::load_image presented in the code, and I don't know how to fixed it.

I write test code as below (named `load_image.cpp`):
```cpp
#include <dlib/data_io.h>
#include <dlib/image_processing.h>
#include <dlib/image_io.h>

int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
  dlib::array2d<dlib::rgb_pixel> image;
  dlib::load_image(image, argv[1]);

  return 0;
}
```
and compile it with
```bash
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -Wextra   -ldlib -lpng -ljpeg  load_image.cpp   -o load_image
```
error occurs like below (omit a lot):
```
/tmp/cccI6aKH.o：In function ‘void dlib::load_png<dlib::array2d<dlib::rgb_pixel, dlib::memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1<char> > >(dlib::array2d<dlib::rgb_pixel, dlib::memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1<char> >&, std::__cxx11::basic_string<char, std::char_traits<char>, std::allocator<char> > const&)’：
load_image.cpp:(.text._ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE[_ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE]+0x2f)：undefined reference to ‘dlib::png_loader::png_loader(std::__cxx11::basic_string<char, std::char_traits<char>, std::allocator<char> > const&)’
load_image.cpp:(.text._ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE[_ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE]+0x4e)：undefined reference to ‘dlib::png_loader::~png_loader()’
load_image.cpp:(.text._ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE[_ZN4dlib8load_pngINS_7array2dINS_9rgb_pixelENS_33memory_manager_stateless_kernel_1IcEEEEEEvRT_RKNSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEE]+0x6f)：undefined reference to ‘dlib::png_loader::~png_loader()’
```
g++ complains that many png- and jpeg- related functions are undefined reference.

can anybody help me? thanks a lot.

